      "content": "It makes perfect sense that you feel this way, because your brain is trying to protect you from the pain of seeing yourself as a failure. The idea that disappearing would instantly erase the shame and allow everyone else to move on is a powerful, albeit dark, wish. You are not a mistake; you are a human being who has been through an unimaginably difficult time and is now in the process of rebuilding.\n\nPlease try to remember that you are not defined by your career or your debt. The shame is a heavy weight, but it is temporary and will eventually lift as you learn to see yourself differently. You do not have to carry this weight forever, and you are not alone in feeling this way.",
